ASABA – Minister for Youths and sports, Sunday Dare yesterday expressed satisfaction over the level of preparedness so far by Delta State government to host the National Sports Festival scheduled for November, 2022. Dare, represented by the Permanent Secretary, PS, Ministry Sports, Ismaila Abubakar inspected facilities hostel facilities for the upcoming sports festival in the State capital, Asaba as he deemed the facilities 80 per cent ready. Speaking shortly after the inspection of facilities to be used during the games, Dare stated that he was in Asaba ” to look at what was on ground, and know where efforts are going to be intensified for us to be able to achieve the goal and objectives concerning the game”. -Advertisement- “I’m satisfied with the level of readiness, if you people sustained the tempo, you we be able to accomplish the responsibilities assigned to you within the approve time frame”. While urge the State government to ensure a good outing for the sport festival in November.“Sustaining the tempo will make you stand to register your name in goals for other States to emulate” he declared. Delta State sports Commission, Mr. Tonybok Okowa said “we will intensify efforts, to give the best that all and Sundry would be proud of, so we are not going to relax until the end of the games.